<!doctype html>
<!--
  facilitator-approved.step-1.mjml — Week 2 after approval: connecting with adopters.
  Source: Drip Emails for facilitators Sign-up - Copy.docx (Email 3).
-->
<html><body style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; color: #1f2937;">
  <h2 style="color: #1f2937;">Connecting with Adopters</h2>
  <p>Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p>
    Now is the exciting time to begin the matching process. You will soon be
    getting to know those who have adopted one or more of the FPGs you are
    working to reach. In meeting those who have committed to adoption, you
    will have a wide array of situations. Some of those adopting are
    individuals who are new to learning about FPGs, while others may be a
    close-culture organization looking to multiply efforts by working with
    you. As you can imagine, discretion and wisdom are key to understanding
    each one.
  </p>

  <p>
    We encourage you to use your usual vetting process to assess each
    adopter. While the matching platform and security system help to make
    appropriate matches, we all need wisdom for working together. In the
    case of any matches that do not suit your organization, please send
    those names back to us and we will re-enter them into the system. If any
    matches are problematic or found to be false in their claims, please let
    us know so we can remove them.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>A helpful tool:</strong> The <em>Global Frontier People Group
    Manual</em> is here for your free use. It is a stand-alone guide that
    can be duplicated with your own logo and used to help your adopters and
    workers better understand the FPG Adoption process.
  </p>

  <p>With you in the work,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>

  <p style="color: #9ca3af; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 32px;">
    Reply "unsubscribe" to stop receiving this series.
  </p>
</body></html>
